*Invitation to Go on Rent Strike*

Management has not responded to our letters and emails requesting rent
relief and a schedule for making repairs for tenants. Therefore we are
encouraging tenants to go on rent strike if they are willing to accept the
risks.

Some tenants are already on rent strike because they cannot afford to pay.
Some tenants may be able to go on a legal rent strike to demand repairs.
Other tenants may decide to voluntarily rent strike in solidarity with
tenants who cannot afford to pay. *If you are already not paying rent, or
deciding to go on rent strike, you should follow guidelines and prepare for
a possible appearance in court. *We do not have legal representation, we
are not lawyers, and we cannot give legal advice. We encourage you to speak
to a lawyer if you are unsure. We have attached several resources below.

Yesterday we distributed red fabric to all apartments. If you want to
announce to other tenants that you're rent striking, please display it in
your courtyard-side window.

